1 _OID bb7617f5-052d-4ca5-bf56-f7cdd6ed7433
1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;JAMES AVERY THOMAS was born in Marengo County, Alabama in 1812. According to the 1850 and 1860 censuses, he was born in 1816 in TN or 1818 in GA. Perhaps he did not know himself
2 CONC . James came to Texas before 1835. At Montgomery County in 1842 he married *AMANDA WHEELER, daughter of *HENRY H. WHEELER and *MARY ANN SAWYER who were neighbors of the Thomas family in Alabama. It also appears that they were neighbors in Georgia
2 CONC , all having arrived in Texas within a short time of each other. James and Amanda settled in Roans Prarie in Grimes County though at the time they first came there, Roans Prarie was in Montgomery County. James was a farmer.&amp;nbsp; James died 2
2 CONC 8 Apr 1865 and is buried at Mustang Prarie. Amanda died 05 Sep 1896 at Mustang Prarie. The cemetery is located 100 yards from the Walker County line, 16 miles west of Huntsville, Texas, off Highway 30.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp
2 CONC ;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font&gt;&lt;font size="+1" color="#0000a0"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;James Thomas and Amanda Wheeler Thomas&amp;#39; Children&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;child&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&
2 CONC lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;born&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;married&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;died&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"
2 CONC &gt;Phebe M&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;1853&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Willis Fulton&lt;/font&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;John Henry&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;1846&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#00
2 CONC 00a0"&gt;Betty Thornton&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;1928&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Sam&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;1862&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Sarah Jane Reed&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a
2 CONC 0"&gt;1888&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Archie&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;1860&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Mollie Coleman&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;1945&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Mack&
2 CONC lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;1857&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Jennie Thompson&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;1937&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;C. Dave&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;1855&lt;/font&
2 CONC gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Mallie McGilberry&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;1942&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Katherine&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;1850&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;John Morris&lt;/fon
2 CONC t&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;1938&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;*Francis Marion&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;1852&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;*Susan Mullens&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;1922&lt;/font&
2 CONC gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;&lt;font size="+1"&gt;1850 Texas Census &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;- &lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Grimes County&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Jame
2 CONC s Thomas age 34 m TN&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;(he was born in GA, or AL not TN)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Amanda 24 f TN&lt;/strong&gt; (she was bor
2 CONC n in GA)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Phebe M. 7 f TX John 4 m TX&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Samuel A. J. 2 m TX&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;
2 CONC /strong&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Amanda C. J. 6/12 f TX&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;H. H. Wheeler 50 m NC&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;br&gt;&
2 CONC lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mary Ann Wheeler 15 f AL &lt;/strong&gt;(Granddaughter of Henry H. Wheeler)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;*JAMES and *AMANDA are listed as being unable to read or write. Thei
2 CONC r property is valued at $600. In the household is HENRY H. WHEELER, Amanda&amp;#39;s father. Mary Ann Wheeler is Amanda&amp;#39;s neice, daughter of her brother, John Wheeler. John lives two farms away from his sister Amanda with his wife Elizabet
2 CONC h and son Joseph Jr. but he denied paternity of the daughter living with Amanda. John listed his occupation as &amp;quot;none&amp;quot;. Henry Wheeler&amp;#39;s wife, Mary Ann Sawyer, does not appear on any census.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;b
2 CONC r&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;&lt;font size="+1"&gt;1860 Texas Census&lt;/font&gt;-Bedias, Grimes County&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;J. Thomas 42 m GA farmer 480 - 700&amp;n
2 CONC bsp;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Amanda 31 f GA keeping house&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Pheoby 17 f&amp;nbsp; TX&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;John 14 m&amp;nb
2 CONC sp; TX&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Samuel 12 m TX&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Catherine 10 f&amp;nbsp; TX&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Jane 8 f&amp;nb
2 CONC sp; TX&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Charles 4 m TX&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;McGowan 2 m TX&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Archie 9/12 m TX&amp;nbsp;&l
2 CONC t;/font&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Willis Fulton 21 m TX (he married Pheoby above)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Elizabeth Wheeler 35&amp;nbsp; f AL Insane, Pauper&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;str
2 CONC ong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Elizabeth Wheeler was the sister-in-law of Amanda. Amanda&amp;#39;s brother John had her declared insane. James&amp;#39; real estate was worth $480 and his personal property was worth $700. Jane and McGowan do no
2 CONC t appear on future censuses. Notice that Amanda lists her state of birth as GA.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;&lt;font size="+1"&gt;1870 Texas Census - Grimes County&lt;/font&gt
2 CONC ;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Amanda Thomas 43 f&amp;nbsp; GA&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Marion 16 m TX&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;David&amp;nbsp;&amp;nb
2 CONC sp; 14 m TX&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Sam&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; 12 m TX&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Archie&amp;nbsp; 10 m TX&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&l
2 CONC t;font color="#0000a0"&gt;By the 1870 Census, James Avery had died, and *FRANCIS MARION THOMAS appears as the 16 year old Marion. For some reason, the dates in&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;the 187
2 CONC 0 census are in error by two years for Amanda and Marion.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Source: &lt;span&gt;&lt;font color="#366388"&gt;http://www.fortunecity.com/tinpan/nirvana/621/thomas.htm&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</l
