1 _OID e8193fda-fd6a-4eed-b3e7-342ce6019ddc
1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;&lt;font size="+2"&gt;THE THOMAS FAMILY&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;&lt;font size="-
2 CONC 1"&gt;The * (asterisk) beside the name denotes ancestral line of Charlotte Sandel Beck&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;The THOMAS surname is common throughout the United States an
2 CONC d there were many branches in the early years of the southern states as well. There are several Thomas lines that are likely to be our the ancestors but as of this writing, they are unproven. The Thomas ancestral line we descend from begins with *J
2 CONC OHN THOMAS and his wife, *PHEOBE SPRINGER , both born about 1784. Their roots begin in the state of South Carolina. Three Thomas men, David, John, and John Nelson are recorded in censuses there and again in Georgia, Alabama and finally in Texas, al
2 CONC l at the same times and places. Their relationship to each other has never been proven.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;A Warren County, Georgia deed of 1799 indicates that John Thomas and hi
2 CONC s wife Pheobe sold to James George, 120 acres on Middle Creek. Another deed dated 1802 mentions a Widow Thomas as adjoining landowner to McCullers land. In 1806, McCullers sold land adjoining Thomas SPRINGER and David THOMAS.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/stron
2 CONC g&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;In 1805 the State of Georgia held a land lottery where land was given to encourage settlement. Land in Warren county was awarded to David Thomas, John Thomas, John Nelson Thomas an
2 CONC d Thomas Springer. Both John Thomas&amp;#39; had two draws, indicating that they were married men. The John in Breed&amp;#39;s District was number 904, the John in Neal&amp;#39;s District was 908, David Thomas was number 909. The same David Thoma
2 CONC s family moved to Texas and ended up in the same area at the same time as our John Thomas family. It is likely that John and David were brothers, or at least cousins.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#000
2 CONC 0a0"&gt;Pheobe&amp;#39;s Springer&amp;#39;s parentage has not been discovered. The land information may be useful because people in that time frame tended to marry their near neighbors. It is therefore possible that Pheobe is the daughter or near r
2 CONC elative of Thomas Springer.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;At least three of John and Pheobe Thomas&amp;#39;s older children list their place of birth as Georgia.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt
2 CONC ; &lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;&lt;font size="+1"&gt;Children of John Thomas and Pheobe Springer Thomas&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Sentha&amp;nbsp;&l
2 CONC t;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt; born 1802, GA&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;born in Georgia&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;N
2 CONC ancy&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt; born 1803, GA&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Betsy&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt; bor
2 CONC n 1805, GA&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;born in Georgia&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Polly&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt; born 18
2 CONC 07, GA&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;married Joseph Henson&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Lucy&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt; born 1
2 CONC 810&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;married William Morris&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;*JAMES&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt; born 1
2 CONC 812, AL&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;married *Amanda Wheeler&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;John Nelson&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&
2 CONC gt;born 1815&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;David&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt; born 1816&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#00
2 CONC 00a0"&gt;Selvania&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt; born 1819&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#000099"&gt;married D. P. Lang&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000
2 CONC a0"&gt;Annie&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt; born 1821&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Samuel A. J.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font col
2 CONC or="#0000a0"&gt;born 1823&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;married Jane Reed&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;William&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#
2 CONC 0000a0"&gt; born 1825&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;married Lydia Springer&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#0000a0"&gt;Simeon&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#
