2 CONC r 1818 in GA. Perhaps he did not know himself. James came to Texas before 1835. At Montgomery County in 1842 he married *AMANDA WHEELER, daughter of *HENRY H. WHEELER and *MARY ANN SAWYER who were neighbors of the Thomas family in Alabama. It als
2 CONC o appears that they were neighbors in Georgia, all having arrived in Texas within a short time of each other. James and Amanda settled in Roans Prarie in Grimes County though at the time they first came there, Roans Prarie was in Montgomery County
2 CONC . James was a farmer.&amp;nbsp; James died 28 Apr 1865 and is buried at Mustang Prarie. Amanda died 05 Sep 1896 at Mustang Prarie. The cemetery is located 100 yards from the Walker County line, 16 miles west of Huntsville, Texas, off Highway 30.&lt
